dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu b Botha 28 (28b 5x4 0x6 46m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: what a start! Done him all ends up. Taibu played all round a straightish ball and it went through the gate. Every batsman knows the horror that lies through the gate and Botha is delighted as it rattles the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Johan Botha player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Johan Botha player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine b Botha 24 (35b 3x4 0x6 40m) SR: 68.57

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Through the dreaded gate again! Pitched and zipped off the track, Ervine was playing across it and it clipped the top of off stump. Botha tries to to leap to celebrate but his knee is still hurting and he ends up collapsed in a heap. Smith can't hold back his laughter!

headshotImage.caption: Rusty Theron player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rusty Theron player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Rusty rattles the stumps this time! Zimbabwe collapsing! Nothing delivery, just back of a length outside off stump but a tame push finds the inside edge and it goes on to the stumps!

image.caption: Shingirai Masakadza

dismissalComment.html: Theron strikes! Middle stump out the ground! Theron aims a yorker, and lands it perfectly, clipping the boot and ricochetting on to middle
that'll be all! Theron finds some extra bounce, Nicolson ends a miserable day be gloving behind and South Africa have recorded their biggest ODI win

headshotImage.caption: Keith Dabengwa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Keith Dabengwa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Parnell strikes! Top bowling! Fired in full and straight, Dabengwa over-balanced as he tried to flick to leg, ended up in an ugly heap as he was trapped in front
"the end is nigh," cries the commentator without a hint of hyperbole, Cremer gets a short ball but the attempted pull finds a top edge that loops gently into the hands of Amla. Good work from Parnell

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Theron b Tsotsobe 5 (5b 1x4 0x6 7m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Taylor is gone, and Tsotsobe has struck in his first over! it was short and climbing just outside off, Taylor looked to go over third man with the late upper cut, but does not get enough distance on the shot and it settles in to the hands of Theron at third man, who takes it on the boundary edge, good well-judged catch

commentTextItems.html: that'll be all! Theron finds some extra bounce, Nicolson ends a miserable day be gloving behind and South Africa have recorded their biggest ODI win

commentPostTextItems.html: Right, that's all from me, Sahil Dutta, and Abhishek Purohit, thanks for all the emails. For a final word on the game do check out Liam Brickhill's bulletin which will be ready shortly.

JP Duminy is named man of the match and declares that he's 'pretty happy' with his form. The man of the series is AB de Villiers, who seems surprisingly nervous as he accepts his award. He says he has 'a lot of work do with the gloves' and insists he's 'going to work very hard at it'.

South Africa win by 272 runs and complete 3-0 series win. Tough day for Zimbabwe here, they've fought bravely with the bat until today when, faced with an impossible 400 target, they slumped to 127 all out. Fair to say it was a rout today, South Africa - led by twin hundreds from de Villiers and Duminy - were might impressive.

commentTextItems.html: classic No. 11 drive, plenty of loose movements and surprise that ball hit bat
big appeal from the fielder, nothing from the bowler, who clearly has a firmer grasp of the rules because it came off the inside edge

dismissalText.commentary: Shingi Masakadza b Theron 14 (12b 0x4 2x6 13m) SR: 116.66

commentTextItems.html: Theron strikes! Middle stump out the ground! Theron aims a yorker, and lands it perfectly, clipping the boot and ricochetting on to middle
steered to third man for a single
Duminy hits the stumps! But only with his body as he tried to slide in and under-arm flick the ball, made a hash of the throw but he cleaned up the stumps with his body
wow! Get this guy up the order! Botha drops just a fraction short and Masakadza clatters it miles over midwicket

commentTextItems.html: back to careful defence
bosh! 'Av it! Bit of air from Botha, and for once Masakadza unwinds his big backlift to send this over mid-on for six
careful, pub-denying defence from Masakadza
you have to admire Masakadza's discipline, giving nothing away here
Botha has settled on a lovely length and line and Masakadza can do nothing but block
beaten again, good stuff from Parnell, slipping this past the outside edge, he deserves to finish this off quickly

commentTextItems.html: fuller, straighter, blocked. What  more can I say?
oh rats, after all that praise he bangs in a long-hop, Utseya is too good to miss out and thumps a boundary to deep square
there is a lot to like about this Parnell spell, this is the best he's been all series, quick and with the angle across the right-hander beating the outside edge
very correctly worked to mid-off
steered to point who for some reason spills a routine stop
squeezed away off the inside half of the bat

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine b Botha 24 (35b 3x4 0x6 40m) SR: 68.57

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Through the dreaded gate again! Pitched and zipped off the track, Ervine was playing across it and it clipped the top of off stump. milestones.description: Duminy and de Villiers's 219-run partnership is SA's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 186 between Albie Morkel and de Villiers
South Africa's 273-run win against Zimbabwe is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 221-run win against Netherlands
